A '''mock election''' is an [[election]] organized for educational or transformative purposes.

== Mock election for educational purposes ==

[[Secondary school]]s organise mock elections to introduce [[youth|young people]] to the concept of elections before they have reached their [[voting age]]. The elections will give the participants an understanding of [[democracy]], the role of government and parliament.
The experience of the mock elections plays a role in stimulating future young voters to cast their ballot.

== Mock election for change to democratic elections ==

As a way to introduce democratic [[elections in Bhutan]], in preparation for the [[Bhutanese general election, 2008|Bhutanese general election]] in 2008, a mock election was held on April 21, 2007 to prepare the Bhutanese for the imminent change to democracy

